Features:

    1. LLama Server Parameter llamacpp fine-tuning
        - Qwen3.5-27B-Q4_K_M
        - Qwen3.5-27B-IQ4_XS
        - Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Q4_K_M

    2. Update Management of llamacpp (pulling latest from GitHub release)
        - Central user control from homebrain dashboard
        - OpenClaw offers update management through OpenClaw dashboad, not required in homebrain dashboard

    3: MCP Server
        - Protonmail
        - Nextcloud

    4. Clean up: Fully remove RPi5 AI feature: No GPU, and insufficient compute, therefore no local inference, no OpenClaw.
        - The user shall not see any "Enable AI Assistant" option, reserved for "HomeBrain"
        - This reduces internal complexity, and enhances robustness, stability.
        - Summary: HomeBrain AI Assistant is OPT-OUT, HomeCloud (RPi5) offers no AI Assistant Option.
        - Test of RPi4 test target

    5. Homebrain localhost-only deployment (no tunnel) option
        - access nextcloud, homeassistant on localhost, nextcloud now gives untrusted endpoint or sth like this error
        - E2E, alredy supported from provisioning onwards

    6. Hardening: Instance shall be always-on (auto boot if on power)
        - Watchdog?

    7. Polish up homebrain dashboard:
        - Additional system stats (uptime, cpu, gpu temp, gpu vram, gpu load)
        - Extend logging view to OpenClaw, llamacpp

    8. Backup: Include OpenClaw Config and Agent Workspace


Issues:
    1. OpenClaw GW API key should be persistent, not regenerated every session.
        - Preferably, the during deployment generated Master password shall also apply to OpenClaw, no dedicated key for the user to remember
    2. OpenClaw whatsapp channel should be restricted to only incoming messages from specified numbers, not default all - consider in whatsapp pairing in homebrain dashboard
    3. Backup shows nvme0n1 as potential backup drive
    4. User and paths mingled
        - Project path: /home/admin/ --> /opt/homebrain/
        - User: admin --> homebrain (keep homebrain, instead of creating new user)
    5. When switching models from homebrain dashboard, this breaks the openclaw configuration:
